    <stitle>PRE-DELIVERY/QUALITY INSPECTION INSTRUCTION MANUAL FOR 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 MODELS -
        7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 Model INSPECTION INSTRUCTIONS (REPORT S00023) - CHASSIS INSPECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="5">
        <title>CHASSIS INSPECTION</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Verify or Inspect...</emph>
        </para>
        <para>21.
            <emph type="italic">Cab air suspension operation</emph>.
        </para>
        <para>22.
            <emph type="italic">Chassis Air/Brake/Fuel hoses, lines, piping are clear from moving parts, sharp edges,
                heat sources, and chafing.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Brake lines.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel hoses and pipes from fuel tank to engine.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Clamps, clips, and straps are properly secured and positioned.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>23.
            <emph type="italic">Starter/alternator cable end tightness, battery cable routing, support and clearance.
                Battery state of charge: 12.6 volts minimum.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Visually inspect power and ground cables from batteries to starter motor.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Visually inspect power cable from starter to alternator.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Clamps, clips, and straps are properly secured and positioned.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Secure cables and add tie straps as necessary.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Charge batteries to 12.6 volts.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>24.
            <emph type="italic">Manual transmission, transfer case, and drive axle oil levels as equipped.</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Clean debris from fill plug area.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>With the vehicle on level ground, remove each fill plug and verify that the fluid is filled to the
                    bottom of the filler hole.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Add fluid if needed. Refer to the Owners Manual for specifications.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <figure id="f1000407" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. Proper Rear Axle Oil Level</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FILLER PLUG</callout1>
                <callout1>2. OIL LEVEL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>25.
            <emph type="italic">Lubricate chassis (and fifth wheel if applicable).</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Lubricate all components with zerk fittings.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Refer to the Owners Manual for proper lubrication points and specifications.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Lubricate 5th wheel, if applicable. Also be sure to close the jaw and then separate the locking
                    jaw from the wedge with a screwdriver and install grease into the gap so that the contact surface
                    between the two parts is well lubricated. This will keep the two parts from sticking together and
                    locking up the jaw mechanism.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <figure id="f1000910" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg10/G1000912.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>26.
            <emph type="italic">Re-torque all spring U-bolts to specifications (including lift axle if applicable).
            </emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Refer to the Torque Chart for specifications.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
