        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Excessive tightening of the wheel nuts will elongate the bolt and deform the contact surface of
                    the nut resulting in an incorrect torque setting. Never use lubricants on the wheel nuts or studs.
                    Always tighten dry.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <para>28.
            <emph type="italic">Re-torque axle flange nuts and driveshaft U-joint retaining bolts/nuts if removed for
                shipping.
            </emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">For axle shafts</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Make sure new gaskets have been installed on each axle removed by the transport carrier.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Tighten the nuts in a star pattern to the specified torque to ensure that axle flanges are
                    properly seated. Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="t1000405">Table 5</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">For U-joint bolts/nuts</emph>
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Inspect slip joint boot for damage.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Insure that the removed U-joint is properly seated in position.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Tighten bolts/nuts to specification.
                    <emph type="bold">NOTE: U-joint strap retaining bolts have a thread locking patch; they may be used
                        one time only.
                    </emph>
                    Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="t1000906">Table 6</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
