        </figure>
        <para>31.
            <emph type="italic">Attach trailer air lines, wiring harness, and secure vertical exhaust pipe if
                equipped</emph>.
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Attach and secure trailer air lines and electrical cord when supplied with tractor as loose
                    parts.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Vertical exhaust stack tailpipes - insertion, alignment, torque</para>
                <seqlist>
                    <item>
                        <para>Vertical exhaust stacks should be fully inserted into exhaust pipe</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Exhaust stacks should be properly aligned if applicable</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Clamps should be tight and secure, and installed in overlapping area between upper and
                            lower stacks
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Torque Specifications:</para>
                        <randlist type="bullet">
                            <item>
                                <para>Aluminized band, bright hardware - 44 to 59 ft-lbs.</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>409 Stainless band, dull gray hardware - 35 to 46 ft-lbs.</para>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <para>If in doubt, torque to 46 ft-lbs.</para>
                            </item>
                        </randlist>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Correct as needed.</para>
                    </item>
                </seqlist>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
